JOHANNESBURG - Christopher Panayiotou has been found guilty of plotting the murder of his wife Jayde. His co-accused, Sinethemba Nenembe and Zolani Sibeko have been dealt the same fate. READ: Video recording ruled admissible in Panayiotou murder trial Judge Dayalin Chetty delivered his verdict a short while ago. Jayde Panayioutou was shot dead in a hit in 2015. She was kidnapped outside her home in Port Elizabeth and her body was found in a veld, just outside Uitenhage a day later. A fourth suspect, the man who is thought to have pulled the trigger, died before the trial began.
